archimate:ArchimateDiagramModel.name: NexSyS Business Context within a Cloud environment
archimate:ArchimateDiagramModel.documentation: An attempt to identify where business relationships stands in order to identified requirements and constraints to consider from a security point of view.

children.content:
Contract to be managed with Microsoft Azure: at NexSys Level, ADS level or Airbus Group Level?
At this stage, On boarding to be done by NexSys Project with the support of IM.
CleanSky is not concerned by this contract. ADS NexSys is to ensure that PMR Quality of Service and security is ensured, consumming properly the services provided by Microsoft.

Delivering the service as part of the CleanSky2 Project Description of Work - related to the associated DoW from contractual point of view. Will also a service to be delivered in CleanSky3 but the project is not yet defined and constract is not yet signed. So what will be the rules to be applied, who will be the future client/user?
Ownership: ADS which developed this service through the NexSys Internal Project?
